# Rules Repository — Structure

**Rules version:** 1.0.0 (frontmatter em `global-rules.mdc`, `project-rules.mdc`, `context-rules.mdc`). Ao alterar regras de forma relevante, incrementar e documentar no PR.

Rules are organized by **layer** and **concern**. Cursor applies them by file context (`globs`) or globally (`alwaysApply: true`).

---

## Três níveis (consolidados)

| Nível | Arquivo | Conteúdo |
|-------|---------|----------|
| **1. Global** | `global-rules.mdc` | Sempre aplicado: papel da IA, prioridades, qualidade de código, segurança universal, princípios de arquitetura. |
| **2. Project** | `project-rules.mdc` | Regras do projeto Innexar: stack, arquitetura detalhada, API, testes, DevOps, domínio (SaaS, auth, billing). |
| **3. Context** | `context-rules.mdc` | Por contexto: Frontend (React/Next/TS/Tailwind), Backend (FastAPI/Python), Database, Segurança sensível, DevOps. |

Esses 3 arquivos reúnem a informação de todas as regras por nível. As regras em subpastas (core/, frontend/, backend/, etc.) continuam ativas e podem ser usadas para ativação por `globs`.

---

## Core (always or broad)

- `core/architecture.mdc` — Clean architecture, layers, max file size
- `core/coding-style.mdc` — Naming, function size, readability
- `core/base-principles.mdc` — Global AI behavior and priorities
- `core/clean-code.mdc` — Constants, DRY, single responsibility, naming (Awesome)
- `core/codequality.mdc` — AI behavior: file-by-file edits, no apologies, preserve code (Awesome)
- `core/testing.mdc` — Unit/integration tests, regression, coverage

## Frontend

- `frontend/react.mdc` — React, hooks, components, a11y (*.tsx, *.jsx)
- `frontend/next.mdc` — Next.js app/pages
- `frontend/tailwind.mdc` — Tailwind usage
- `frontend/components.mdc` — UI structure and reuse

## Backend

- `backend/fastapi.mdc` — FastAPI, types, Pydantic, auth, tests (*.py, api, routers)
- `backend/api.mdc` — API design, responses, validation
- `backend/services.mdc` — Service layer, business logic

## Database

- `database/postgres.mdc` — PostgreSQL, indexes, N+1
- `database/migrations.mdc` — Schema changes, migrations only
- `database/repository.mdc` — Repository pattern, data access

## Security

- `security/general.mdc` — Sanitization, injection, XSS, secrets (alwaysApply)
- `security/secure-development-principles.mdc` — No raw input, no secrets in code (alwaysApply)
- `security/owasp.mdc` — OWASP-oriented practices (api, auth)
- `security/secure-sql.mdc` — Parameterized queries, no SQL injection
- `security/path-traversal.mdc` — Never user input in file paths
- `security/dangerous-flows.mdc` — Trace user input to avoid injection/unsafe use
- `security/ssrf.mdc` — Do not let user input control outbound URLs
- `security/xxe.mdc` — Disable DTDs/external entities in XML parsing

## DevOps

- `devops/docker.mdc` — Dockerfile, compose, images
- `devops/ci-env.mdc` — CI/CD, env, logging
- `devops/gitflow.mdc` — Branches, commits, PRs, semantic versioning (Awesome)

## Languages

- `languages/typescript.mdc` — TypeScript strict, no any (*.ts, *.tsx)
- `languages/python.mdc` — Python type hints, Pydantic, secure Python (*.py)

## Domain (Innexar)

- `domain/saas-multi-tenant.mdc` — Tenant isolation
- `domain/billing.mdc` — Stripe / payments
- `domain/auth.mdc` — Auth and authorization

